      <section class="card hero">
        <h1>How to Get Investment for Online Purposes — practical roadmap</h1>
        <p class="lead">Whether you're building an ecommerce site, mobile app, SaaS, content network, or digital agency — this guide shows proven ways to attract funding and manage investor relationships.</p>

        <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:12px">
          <a class="cta" href="#lead">Get the Pitch Checklist</a>
          <a class="cta" style="background:#0b74de" href="#platforms">See Funding Platforms</a>
        </div>

        <div class="card" id="steps" style="margin-top:12px">
          <h2 style="margin-top:0">Step-by-Step: Get Investment for Online Purposes</h2>
          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step"><div class="num">1</div><div><strong>Clarify the Use of Funds</strong><p class="small">Be specific — product build, marketing, hiring, inventory, or working capital. Investors fund outcomes, not ideas.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">2</div><div><strong>Validate & Show Traction</strong><p class="small">Launch an MVP, pre-sell, or show user growth/revenue. Traction reduces investor risk and increases valuation.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">3</div><div><strong>Create a Clear Pitch Deck</strong><p class="small">Problem, solution, market size, model, traction, team, ask & use of funds, and a 12-24 month projection.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">4</div><div><strong>Choose Funding Route</strong><p class="small">Pick from bootstrapping, angels, VC, crowdfunding, revenue-based finance, or loans depending on scale & control needs.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">5</div><div><strong>Target & Reach Investors</strong><p class="small">Warm intros, angel networks, LinkedIn outreach, pitch events, accelerators, and crowdfunding campaigns are common channels.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">6</div><div><strong>Negotiate Terms & Close</strong><p class="small">Understand dilution, valuation, investor rights, and provide milestones. Use lawyers for term sheets and SAFE/convertible notes if needed.</p></div></div>

            <div class="step"><div class="num">7</div><div><strong>Deliver & Report</strong><p class="small">Use investor funds as promised, track KPIs, and report monthly/quarterly to maintain trust and unlock future rounds.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
          <h2 style="margin-top:0">Essential Documents & Prep</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>1-page executive summary</li>
            <li>10–12 slide pitch deck</li>
            <li>3–12 month financial projections</li>
            <li>Cap table & current investors</li>
            <li>Product demos, analytics, and customer references</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
          <h2 style="margin-top:0">How to Use Different Funding Types</h2>
          <table>
            <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Best for</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Bootstrapping</td><td>Early control, testing</td><td>Slower growth, limited capital</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Angel Investors</td><td>Seed and mentorship</td><td>Some equity dilution</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Venture Capital</td><td>High growth, scaling</td><td>Significant dilution & expectations</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Crowdfunding</td><td>Product pre-sales & marketing</td><td>Public scrutiny, campaign work</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Revenue-based Finance</td><td>Recurring revenue businesses</td><td>Repayment reduces cashflow</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Bank Loans / Grants</td><td>Capital without equity</td><td>Requires credit/collateral or eligibility</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
