    <section class="card" id="platforms" style="margin-top:20px">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">Where to Find Investors & Funding Online</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Angel networks:</strong> AngelList, local angel groups, industry-focused syndicates.</li>
        <li><strong>VC firms & accelerators:</strong> Apply to relevant accelerators (YC, Techstars) or target VC lists that invest in your stage.</li>
        <li><strong>Crowdfunding:</strong> Use Kickstarter/Indiegogo for consumer products; equity platforms for growth startups.</li>
        <li><strong>Revenue-based financing:</strong> Lighter on equity, good for SaaS with steady MRR.</li>
        <li><strong>Grants & competitions:</strong> Check government or industry grants and startup competitions.</li>
        <li><strong>Strategic partners:</strong> Corporate investors or channel partners who benefit from your growth.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card" id="faq" style="margin-top:18px">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq">
        <details><summary><strong>How much equity should I give away at seed?</strong></summary>
          <p class="small">Typical seed rounds range from 10–25% depending on valuation, stage, and amount raised. Avoid over-dilution early; focus on hitting traction milestones.</p>
        </details>

        <details><summary><strong>When should I bootstrap vs raise outside capital?</strong></summary>
          <p class="small">Bootstrap when you can reach meaningful milestones without external capital. Raise when capital will materially accelerate growth and ROI (e.g., rapid market expansion, hiring key talent, or building capital-intensive products).</p>
        </details>

        <details><summary><strong>How do I approach an investor cold?</strong></summary>
          <p class="small">Cold outreach can work if concise and data-driven: one-sentence intro, quick traction stats, and a clear CTA to a 15-minute call. Warm intros are much more effective.</p>
        </details>

        <details><summary><strong>What metrics investors care about for online businesses?</strong></summary>
          <p class="small">Common metrics: monthly/annual recurring revenue (MRR/ARR), growth rate, CAC, LTV, churn, gross margin, and unit economics.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

